        {
          "type": "tts",
          "startSec": 0.4,
          "endSec": 5.4625,
          "text": "Kanbus is a high-level, accessible way to run Kanban directly from your repository.",
          "segmentPath": "/Users/ryan.porter/Projects/Kanbus/.videoml/out/intro/env/development/segments/opening--overview--tts--c4a0f42e2675--1.wav",
          "durationSec": 5.0625,
          "rawDurationSec": 5.0625,
          "trimEndSec": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "pause",
          "startSec": 5.4625,
          "endSec": 5.6625000000000005,
          "seconds": 0.2
        },
        {
          "type": "tts",
          "startSec": 5.6625000000000005,
          "endSec": 14.1125,
          "text": "You get a live board and a command line workflow, while everything stays grounded in plain files your team and AI agents can both use.",
          "segmentPath": "/Users/ryan.porter/Projects/Kanbus/.videoml/out/intro/env/development/segments/opening--overview--tts--1eafffb46aba--1.wav",
          "durationSec": 8.45,
          "rawDurationSec": 8.45,
          "trimEndSec": 0
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tts",
      "sceneId": "opening",
      "cueId": "git_bus",
      "startSec": 14.1125,
      "endSec": 28.0625,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "tts",
          "startSec": 14.1125,
          "endSec": 18.762500000000003,
          "text": "Git synchronization is the core idea: use Git as the bus for Kanban boards.",
          "segmentPath": "/Users/ryan.porter/Projects/Kanbus/.videoml/out/intro/env/development/segments/opening--git_bus--tts--c6c93d6f5b34--1.wav",
          "durationSec": 4.65,
          "rawDurationSec": 4.65,
          "trimEndSec": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "pause",
          "startSec": 18.762500000000003,
          "endSec": 18.962500000000002,
          "seconds": 0.2
        },
        {
          "type": "tts",
          "startSec": 18.962500000000002,
          "endSec": 28.0625,
          "text": "Board updates become normal file changes, so review, history, branching, and collaboration work exactly the way your engineering team already expects.",
          "segmentPath": "/Users/ryan.porter/Projects/Kanbus/.videoml/out/intro/env/development/segments/opening--git_bus--tts--fd20551076eb--1.wav",
          "durationSec": 9.1,
          "rawDurationSec": 9.1,
          "trimEndSec": 0
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tts",
      "sceneId": "feature-tour",
      "cueId": "feature_list",
      "startSec": 28.5625,
      "endSec": 44.9625,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "tts",
          "startSec": 28.5625,
          "endSec": 37.05,
          "text": "From there, pick the capabilities you need: an agent-ready CLI, Jira synchronization, local tasks, virtual projects, and Beads compatibility.",
          "segmentPath": "/Users/ryan.porter/Projects/Kanbus/.videoml/out/intro/env/development/segments/feature-tour--feature_list--tts--c93fd74827c9--1.wav",
          "durationSec": 8.4875,
          "rawDurationSec": 8.4875,
          "trimEndSec": 0
        },
        {
          "type": "pause",
          "startSec": 37.05,
          "endSec": 37.25,
          "seconds": 0.2
        },
        {
          "type": "tts",
          "startSec": 37.25,
          "endSec": 44.9625,
          "text": "You also get a VS Code plugin, an integrated wiki, and policy as code so humans and agents operate from one shared workflow.",
          "segmentPath": "/Users/ryan.porter/Projects/Kanbus/.videoml/out/intro/env/development/segments/feature-tour--feature_list--tts--e598b5f5b043--1.wav",
          "durationSec": 7.7125,
